SIMPLE: prodigiously
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Prodigiously
<hw>Pro*di"gious*ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Enormously; wonderfully; astonishingly; <as>as,
<ex>prodigiously</ex> great</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Very much; extremely; <as>as, he was
<ex>prodigiously</ex> pleased</as>.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark>
<rj><au>Pope.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prodigiousness</ent>⟦br⟧
